com.gh.bmd.jrt.android.processor.v11.annotation

Annotation Type V11Proxy


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
@Retention(value=SOURCE)
public @interface V11Proxy
    This annotation is used to indicate interfaces used as templates to generate proxy classes enabling asynchronous calls to the target instance methods, bound to a context lifecycle.

    The target class is specified in the annotation attribute. A proxy class implementing the annotated interface will be generated within the interface package and its name will be obtained by prepending "JRoutineV11Proxy_" to the interface simple name. In case the specific interface is not a top class, the simple name of the outer classes will be prepended to the interface one.
    The routines used for calling the methods will honor the attributes specified in any optional Bind, Timeout, TimeoutAction and Pass, as well as v11 builder annotations defined for each interface method.

    See V4Proxy for support of API levels less than 11.

    Created by davide on 06/05/15.
